{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Abolish the 25% threshold for changes in income to trigger CMS recalculation",
        "additional_details": "Many payers overpay or underpay hundreds or thousands of pounds a year, never get the money back. 25% is too high, and can lead to financial problems, mental health issues, and risk homelessness.",
        "background": "CMS do not recalculate child maintenance awards where incomes change by less than 25%. This can have major consequences on payers' and recipients' lives. CMS has access to HMRC and can request payslips to correct the amount to pay.",
